text.tspan: This graph shows average values from projections from five global models used by the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change. Due to variability among models and among years in a
natural climate system, such graphs are useful for examining trends over time, rather than for precisely predicting monthly or yearly values. For more information on the SNAP program, including
derivation, reliability, and variability among these projections, please visit www.snap.uaf.edu.
